            <div>
                <head>Comments</head>
                <p xml:id="KR2p0028-start">
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0028_tls_001-3a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-19T20:22:55.258+09:00">Being an exhausible (i.e. finite) is a necessary condition of having a dimension.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0028_tls_001-4a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-19T20:24:15.698+09:00">Note the word-play</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0028_tls_001-4a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-19T20:26:35.375+09:00">The existence of names depends on the practice of designating things</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0028_tls_001-4a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-19T21:07:24.424+09:00">Morality depends on moral terminology.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0028_tls_001-7a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-19T23:53:32.88+09:00">More than purely conventional ritual propriety depends on moral rectitude.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0028_tls_001-7a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-19T23:56:05.835+09:00">Goodness depends on aesthetically admirable (abstract) beauty.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0028_tls_001-8a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-19T23:57:44.946+09:00">Goodness depends on sagely wisdom (promoting it).</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0028_tls_001-30a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-20T01:49:53.579+09:00">此 refers to this deliberate act, which is not one of true piety.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0028_tls_001-30a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-20T01:50:53.603+09:00">此 refers to this act of brotherly respect, which is not a an act of true brotherly respect.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0028_tls_001-1a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-20T09:13:48.755+09:00">　【荀子：慎、墨不得進其談】Laozi 甲:   天下之物生於有，　                                    "All the creatures in the world arise from being,                                                                                                                                                                                    　                                有生於亡。　                                    and being itself arises from where there was none.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0028_tls_001-2a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-20T09:14:53.234+09:00">graph controversial. Here as nearly everywhere I follow the 劉釗 釋文。</seg>
                </p>
